title: So You Think You Can Dance Canada Season 3
description:
"So You Think You Can Dance Canada" was a dance reality show and competition that aired on the CTV television network for four seasons. It was hosted by MuchMusic VJ and ETalk correspondent Leah Miller.

The series was based on the original American TV series "So You Think You Can Dance". Auditions for the first season began April 7, 2008 in Vancouver, British Columbia and ended in Toronto, Ontario on June 8, 2008. The show premiered on September 11, 2008 beginning with the Toronto auditions.

The first show in season 3 aired on August 15, 2010. The first six broadcasts covered the auditions which brought the field down to 22 dancers. There were a total of 24 broadcasts in season 3.

In addition to the winner receiving the title of Canada's Favourite Dancer and $100,000, both the winner and runner-up received a Mazda 2 automobile
